    <div class="post-content animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 0.2s;">

        <p>Welcome to <strong>Parth Posts</strong>. Your privacy matters to me. This policy explains what information this site collects, why it's collected, and how it's used. By using this site, you agree to the practices described below.</p>

        <h2>Information I Collect</h2>
        <p>This blog does not require you to create an account or submit personal details to read content. However, some data may be collected automatically or through third-party tools:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> Pages visited, time spent, referring URLs, and browser/device type, collected anonymously via analytics tools.</li>
            <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> Small files stored by your browser to remember your theme preference (light/dark mode) and support analytics. No personally identifying cookies are set by this site directly.</li>
            <li><strong>Contact information:</strong> If you reach out via email or LinkedIn, I receive and store only what you choose to send me.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>This site may use the following third-party services, each with their own privacy policies:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — for understanding traffic and content performance. Google may collect anonymised usage data. See <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
            <li><strong>Google AdSense</strong> — to display relevant advertisements. Google uses cookies to serve ads based on prior visits to this and other websites. See <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Ad Policy</a>.</li>
            <li><strong>Google Fonts</strong> — fonts are loaded from Google's servers, which may log your IP address as part of the request.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How Your Information Is Used</h2>
        <p>Any data collected is used solely to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Understand how readers find and use this blog, so I can improve it.</li>
            <li>Display relevant advertisements that help support the site.</li>
            <li>Respond to messages or collaboration inquiries you initiate.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>I do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with any third parties beyond the services listed above.</p>

        <h2>Cookies & Your Choices</h2>
        <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings. Disabling cookies may affect minor site features like theme preference persistence. To opt out of Google Analytics tracking, you can use the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>. To manage ad personalisation, visit <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ad Settings</a>.</p>

        <h2>External Links</h2>
        <p>Posts on this blog may link to external websites. I am not responsible for the privacy practices or content of those sites. I encourage you to review their privacy policies before sharing any personal information.</p>

        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>This site is not directed at children under the age of 13 and does not knowingly collect any information from them.</p>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>This privacy policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be reflected on this page with a revised "Last updated" date. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about this privacy policy, feel free to reach out at <a href="mailto:parth4tiwari@gmail.com">parth4tiwari@gmail.com</a> or via <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/parth4tiwari" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>.</p>

